						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I probably chose the name &quot;halt&quot; because it's one word. It's really a mode flag, telling whether the linear counter is reloaded or decremented on linear clocks.</div><br /><br />I might still be a bit confused, but maybe it could be called something like &quot;linear counter initialization flag&quot; (or &quot;linear counter reload flag&quot;), since it indicates whether the linear counter should be initialized on the next linear clock. It's a bit more verbose, but &quot;halt&quot; is easy to confuse with the length counter halt flag, and might also give you the idea that it halts the waveform generator.<br /><br />Edit: &quot;linear counter setup flag&quot; or &quot;linear counter load flag&quot; might be even better.</div>

